cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.HC, cs.DB

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses a deep-learning approach to predicting readmissions and a new deep-learning model called a point-wise linear model. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses deep learning to predict readmissions and provides an automatic patient stratification to explain cohorts of readmitted patients. 
- cs.CE (Computational Epidemiology): The paper discusses the cost of heart failures in the United States and how predictive analysis can decrease costs due to readmission of heart failure patients. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper discusses the importance of explaining the decisions behind readmission predictions and analyzing feature importance. 
- cs.DB (Databases): The paper uses a dataset to evaluate the approach and analyze feature importance.
